==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Historian
<hw>His*to"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>historien</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A writer of history; a
chronicler; an annalist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Even the <qex>historian</qex> takes great liberties with
facts.</q> <rj><qau>Sir J. Reynolds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One versed or well informed in history.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great captains should be good <qex>historians</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

